<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n54135c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54135c">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54135c"> 135(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> bloodygrooved sword / corselet</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In battle the weapons of defence were helmet, corselet and shield. The shields were of wood with a heavy iron boss in the centre. <mark>The corselets</mark> were made of iron rings, leather, or thick cloth. The weapons of offence were mainly sword, spear and battle-axe. The sword was of the two-edged type and usually had <mark>a shallow depression along the middle of the blade, known as the blood-channel</mark>. <small> Allen Mawers, <a name="VIK2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#VIK2"><cite title="source">The Vikings</cite></a> (1913) 101</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
